{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7b7f208d-3ed0-4459-9406-6a32d5f3d1a8","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so here's general guidance for the switch:\n\n### Changes needed for NuGet Trusted Publishing (OIDC)\n\n**1. NuGet.org setup:**\n- Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add a new trusted publisher, linking your GitHub repo, branch/tag pattern, and workflow file path\n\n**2. Workflow changes:**\n\n```yaml\n# Add permissions at the job level\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token\n      contents: read\n\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      # ... build & pack steps ...\n\n      # Replace your current push step:\n      #   dotnet nuget push ... --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}\n      # With:\n      - name: Push to NuGet\n        run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n          --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n| Before (API key) | After (OIDC) |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` | No secret needed |\n| `--api-key` flag | No `--api-key` flag |\n| No special permissions | `id-token: write` required |\n\n**3. Clean up:**\n- Remove the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo settings once verified\n\nThe `dotnet` CLI automatically detects the OIDC token from the GitHub Actions environment when `id-token: write` is set and no API key is provided. NuGet.org validates the token against your trusted publisher configuration.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"93f9ce2c-fee7-4f7b-b4be-b0a5586c7da9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. The user doesn't have an existing workflow file in the repo — they're asking a general knowledge question about switching from NuGet API key authentication to OIDC-based trusted publishing. Let me provide guidance.","outputTokens":480},"id":"eef4da2e-3ecc-491c-ac61-f9a899236b79","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:45:14.873Z","parentId":"4fa365f7-768b-4fbe-ac20-fc26c1528133"}
